!import-table --CRIT_Piercing --show
!import-table-item --CRIT_Piercing --Lunge and thrust! Roll damage dice twice and use the higher result. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Piercing --Good hit! Do not roll your damage dice, instead deal the maximum result possible with those dice. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Piercing --Stabbed! Roll your damage dice twice and add them together. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Piercing --Great hit! Roll your damage dice twice and add them together. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Piercing --Swiss cheese! Roll your damage dice twice. Then roll twice on the minor injury chart and use the lesser result. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Piercing --Punctured! Roll your damage dice twice and add them together and roll on the minor injury chart. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Piercing --Cruel prick! Roll your damage dice twice and add them together and receive a Wound point. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Piercing --Run through! Deal twice the maximum result of your damage dice and receive a Wound point. --1 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Piercing --Pierce! Deal the maximum result of your damage dice twice, roll on the minor injury chart, and receive a Wound point. --1 --
